Huh? What was that?

00:01:34.136 --> 00:01:36.138 position:38% line:83% align:start
[CHIAKI]
Makoto, throw the ball!

00:01:36.172 --> 00:01:40.276 position:10% line:83% align:start
Did you guys hear something
just now? Kinda like...

00:01:40.309 --> 00:01:41.410 position:38% line:83% align:start
[CHIAKI]
Hear something?

00:01:41.443 --> 00:01:42.978 position:35% line:83% align:start
[KOUSUKE]
Like what?

00:01:43.811 --> 00:01:45.147 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
Weird...

00:01:47.049 --> 00:01:48.750 position:38% line:83% align:start
[CHIAKI]
C'mon! Toss it!

00:01:52.821 --> 00:01:55.024 position:30% line:89% align:start
Here it comes!

00:01:55.057 --> 00:01:56.158 position:38% line:89% align:start
[grunts]

00:01:56.192 --> 00:01:57.726 position:27% line:89% align:start
[CHIAKI grunts]

00:01:58.861 --> 00:02:00.429 position:38% line:83% align:start
[CHIAKI]
Ah, man!

00:02:01.830 --> 00:02:03.332 position:35% line:83% align:start
[KOUSUKE]
Got it!

00:02:03.365 --> 00:02:04.333 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
Guess what?

00:02:04.366 --> 00:02:05.401 position:35% line:83% align:start
[KOUSUKE]
What?

00:02:05.434 --> 00:02:07.903 position:19% line:89% align:start
Yesterday, I-- Uh, ah!

00:02:07.937 --> 00:02:09.805 position:16% line:89% align:start
I didn't get my pudding.

00:02:09.838 --> 00:02:11.840 position:38% line:83% align:start
[CHIAKI]
Why? What happened?

00:02:11.874 --> 00:02:13.976 position:21% line:83% align:start
[KOUSUKE] I bet your
sister scarfed it down.

00:02:17.213 --> 00:02:20.115 position:13% line:83% align:start
Yeah, and I was saving it
for a special snack.

00:02:20.149 --> 00:02:23.285 position:13% line:83% align:start
Little brat! How dare she
help herself to my stuff!

00:02:25.821 --> 00:02:28.224 position:38% line:83% align:start
[CHIAKI]
Aww, I did it again.

00:02:29.291 --> 00:02:30.259 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MIYUKI]
Sis?

00:02:30.293 --> 00:02:31.461 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:02:31.494 --> 00:02:32.429 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MIYUKI]
Sis?

00:02:32.462 --> 00:02:33.697 position:41% line:89% align:start
H-Huh?

00:02:37.567 --> 00:02:40.135 position:24% line:89% align:start
What the...? Huh?

00:02:40.170 --> 00:02:42.239 position:35% line:83% align:start
[KOUSUKE]
Makoto! Makoto!

00:02:42.272 --> 00:02:43.540 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
What?

00:02:43.573 --> 00:02:45.108 position:35% line:83% align:start
[KOUSUKE]
Heads up!

00:02:47.843 --> 00:02:48.511 position:44% line:89% align:start
Uh?

00:02:48.545 --> 00:02:50.813 position:35% line:89% align:start
[beeping]

00:02:50.846 --> 00:02:52.048 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
Ow!

00:02:52.082 --> 00:02:53.816 position:33% line:89% align:start
That hurt...

00:02:56.553 --> 00:03:00.889 position:38% line:89% align:start
[grunts]

00:03:03.026 --> 00:03:04.361 position:35% line:89% align:start
[screams]

00:03:05.962 --> 00:03:08.131 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MIYUKI]
It's about time you got up.

00:03:17.574 --> 00:03:19.509 position:10% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO] What'd you turn off
the alarm for?!

00:03:19.542 --> 00:03:21.344 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MIYUKI]
Turn it off yourself!

00:03:21.378 --> 00:03:22.545 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
Bye, Mom!

00:03:22.579 --> 00:03:25.148 position:7% line:83% align:start
[NEWS ANCHOR A] Yes, it's July
13, which is a "Nice Day."

00:03:25.181 --> 00:03:25.949 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
I'm in trouble!

00:03:25.982 --> 00:03:27.150 position:27% line:83% align:start
[NEWS ANCHOR B]
What do you mean?

00:03:27.183 --> 00:03:29.587 position:10% line:83% align:start
[NEWS ANCHOR A] Month seven,
day one-three is "Na-I-Su."

00:03:29.620 --> 00:03:31.388 position:24% line:83% align:start
Finally managed to
get up, did you?

00:03:31.421 --> 00:03:32.422 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
Morning, Dad.

00:03:32.455 --> 00:03:33.990 position:44% line:89% align:start
Oh.

00:03:39.195 --> 00:03:39.929 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
Ah!

00:03:39.963 --> 00:03:41.031 position:30% line:89% align:start
Good morning.

00:03:41.064 --> 00:03:42.198 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
I'm outta here!

00:03:42.232 --> 00:03:43.833 position:30% line:83% align:start
Wait, Makoto!
Hang on a second!

00:03:43.867 --> 00:03:45.101 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
What now?

00:03:45.135 --> 00:03:46.036 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MOTHER]
On your way home,

00:03:46.069 --> 00:03:48.071 position:19% line:83% align:start
could you take this to
your Auntie Witch?

00:03:48.104 --> 00:03:49.205 position:10% line:89% align:start
Tell her it's from Grandma.

00:03:49.239 --> 00:03:52.208 position:7% line:83% align:start
No way! I don't wanna lug all
that stuff to school.

00:03:52.242 --> 00:03:53.544 position:10% line:83% align:start
--[MOTHER] One more thing...
--[MAKOTO] Uh?

00:03:53.577 --> 00:03:56.246 position:10% line:83% align:start
[MOTHER] Ask her when she's
going to get married.

00:03:56.280 --> 00:03:58.014 position:38% line:83% align:start
--'Kay.
--Thanks.

00:03:58.048 --> 00:04:00.016 position:35% line:83% align:start
--See ya!
--Bye!

00:04:01.452 --> 00:04:03.086 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MOTHER]
Have a good day.

00:04:15.333 --> 00:04:17.601 position:35% line:83% align:start
[WOMAN A]
Oh, morning, Mako!

00:04:17.635 --> 00:04:19.070 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
G'morning!

00:04:25.409 --> 00:04:29.146 position:16% line:89% align:start
[crossing gates ringing]

00:04:29.180 --> 00:04:32.049 position:21% line:83% align:start
--[bike bell chimes]
--[MAKOTO] Whoa! Oh... Ah!

00:04:32.083 --> 00:04:33.517 position:21% line:83% align:start
--[tires squealing]
--[MAKOTO] Whoa! Oh... Ah!

00:04:33.551 --> 00:04:36.053 position:27% line:89% align:start
[CROWD gasping]

00:04:36.087 --> 00:04:37.221 position:30% line:89% align:start
[MAKOTO sighs]

00:04:37.254 --> 00:04:40.191 position:19% line:83% align:start
Sorry about the ruckus
every morning.

00:04:42.993 --> 00:04:44.595 position:30% line:89% align:start
[CHIAKI hums]

00:04:44.628 --> 00:04:45.896 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
Hey, Chiaki!

00:04:45.930 --> 00:04:46.997 position:33% line:89% align:start
Hey, Makoto.

00:04:47.031 --> 00:04:49.200 position:10% line:83% align:start
Cutting it close. Maybe you
should get up earlier.

00:04:49.233 --> 00:04:51.168 position:24% line:83% align:start
That's priceless,
coming from you.

00:04:51.202 --> 00:04:52.970 position:7% line:89% align:start
Fell back to sleep, didn't ya?

00:04:53.003 --> 00:04:53.971 position:38% line:89% align:start
Shut up!

00:04:54.004 --> 00:04:55.473 position:24% line:83% align:start
[CHIAKI chuckles]
Hey, what's in the basket?

00:04:55.506 --> 00:04:56.407 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
None of your buisness!

00:04:56.440 --> 00:04:58.109 position:38% line:83% align:start
[CHIAKI]
Come on. Tell me.

00:04:58.142 --> 00:05:00.612 position:33% line:89% align:start
[bell rings]

00:05:00.645 --> 00:05:02.146 position:27% line:89% align:start
[MAKOTO panting]

00:05:02.179 --> 00:05:04.181 position:19% line:89% align:start
Barely made it again.

00:05:04.215 --> 00:05:06.551 position:10% line:83% align:start
Why not give us some variety
and be late for a change?

00:05:06.585 --> 00:05:08.152 position:38% line:83% align:start
[CHIAKI]
Why so early, Kousuke?

00:05:08.185 --> 00:05:10.389 position:16% line:83% align:start
Forget to jerk yourself
off this morning?

00:05:10.422 --> 00:05:12.923 position:21% line:89% align:start
Ha, ha. Very funny.

00:05:12.957 --> 00:05:16.561 position:21% line:83% align:start
I made it with extra
time to spare. Look!

00:05:16.595 --> 00:05:18.262 position:7% line:89% align:start
Are we totally lucky or what?

00:05:18.296 --> 00:05:20.131 position:10% line:89% align:start
I'm the lucky one, not you.

00:05:20.164 --> 00:05:22.199 position:35% line:89% align:start
Excuse me.

00:05:22.234 --> 00:05:23.535 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
People say they're out of luck

00:05:23.568 --> 00:05:25.203 position:10% line:89% align:start
when something bad happens,

00:05:25.237 --> 00:05:26.671 position:13% line:83% align:start
I always thought that was
just a figure of speech,

00:05:26.705 --> 00:05:29.974 position:16% line:83% align:start
being lucky or unlucky.
But I guess I'm lucky.

00:05:30.007 --> 00:05:32.110 position:24% line:83% align:start
Now people, why do
you think I was late

00:05:32.144 --> 00:05:33.178 position:13% line:89% align:start
in getting to class today?

00:05:33.211 --> 00:05:34.945 position:27% line:89% align:start
Not a pop quiz!

00:05:34.979 --> 00:05:36.548 position:24% line:83% align:start
[FUKUSHIMA-SENSEI]
Yes, Hayakawa. Correct!

00:05:36.581 --> 00:05:38.417 position:41% line:89% align:start
What?!

00:05:38.450 --> 00:05:41.686 position:21% line:89% align:start
[STUDENTS groaning]

00:05:43.054 --> 00:05:45.991 position:10% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO] I've gotta say, I'm
pretty lucky most of the time.

00:05:46.024 --> 00:05:48.493 position:21% line:83% align:start
Not only lucky, but
I have good instincts, too.

00:05:48.527 --> 00:05:50.662 position:27% line:83% align:start
'Cause of that,
my grades are okay.

00:05:50.695 --> 00:05:53.665 position:16% line:83% align:start
I'm not exactly a brain,
but I'm not an idiot either.

00:05:53.698 --> 00:05:55.634 position:24% line:83% align:start
[FUKUSHIMA-SENSEI]
You have five more minutes.

00:05:57.402 --> 00:05:58.303 position:41% line:89% align:start
Huh?!

00:05:58.336 --> 00:06:02.174 position:16% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO] I'm not dumb...
by most standards.

00:06:02.207 --> 00:06:04.209 position:30% line:89% align:start
Five minutes.

00:06:04.242 --> 00:06:06.311 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
This time doesn't count.

00:06:06.344 --> 00:06:08.413 position:24% line:83% align:start
I'm not especially
skilled in anything...

00:06:08.447 --> 00:06:12.484 position:16% line:83% align:start
...but I'm not a walking
disaster, either.

00:06:12.517 --> 00:06:13.418 position:24% line:89% align:start
When I look back,

00:06:13.452 --> 00:06:16.455 position:16% line:83% align:start
I don't remember making
any huge mess-ups.

00:06:18.323 --> 00:06:20.693 position:30% line:89% align:start
[MAKOTO yelps]

00:06:23.128 --> 00:06:24.664 position:24% line:89% align:start
[STUDENTS scream]

00:06:24.697 --> 00:06:26.298 position:33% line:83% align:start
[TEACHER A]
What're you standing there for?!

00:06:26.331 --> 00:06:27.299 position:13% line:89% align:start
Get the fire extinguisher!

00:06:27.332 --> 00:06:28.601 position:33% line:83% align:start
[STUDENT A]
Just a second!

00:06:28.634 --> 00:06:30.470 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
Again, an exception.

00:06:30.503 --> 00:06:32.137 position:7% line:89% align:start
Are you sure you're all right?

00:06:32.170 --> 00:06:34.105 position:24% line:83% align:start
Yeah, but I singed
my bangs a bit.

00:06:34.139 --> 00:06:35.408 position:35% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
Normally, I'm pretty careful,

00:06:35.441 --> 00:06:37.275 position:5% line:89% align:start
so I've never been hurt too bad.

00:06:37.309 --> 00:06:39.244 position:27% line:83% align:start
And I make sure
not to get involved

00:06:39.277 --> 00:06:41.581 position:7% line:89% align:start
in complicated relationships.

00:06:41.681 --> 00:06:42.782 position:27% line:89% align:start
[STUDENT yells]

00:06:42.815 --> 00:06:44.417 position:24% line:89% align:start
[STUDENTS chatter]

00:06:44.450 --> 00:06:46.385 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
Jeez! Do you mind?!

00:06:46.419 --> 00:06:49.455 position:38% line:89% align:start
Get off!

00:06:49.489 --> 00:06:52.492 position:13% line:89% align:start
Come on, you idiot! Move!

00:06:52.525 --> 00:06:56.462 position:16% line:83% align:start
Ah. Big man's up to bat.
He's battin' .412 this year.

00:06:56.496 --> 00:06:59.165 position:21% line:83% align:start
Ah. He's undefeated
at the plate--

00:06:59.198 --> 00:07:01.300 position:33% line:89% align:start
Oh! Ah, man!

00:07:01.334 --> 00:07:03.536 position:35% line:89% align:start
[laughing]

00:07:03.569 --> 00:07:05.204 position:33% line:89% align:start
Little jerk.

00:07:05.238 --> 00:07:07.039 position:10% line:89% align:start
You think you're funny, huh?

00:07:07.073 --> 00:07:08.674 position:16% line:83% align:start
--All right, funny man.
--[MORIKO] I don't think

00:07:08.708 --> 00:07:10.710 position:16% line:83% align:start
this has anything to do
with you blood type horoscope.

00:07:10.743 --> 00:07:13.045 position:13% line:83% align:start
[SEKIMI] Yeah, but it says
they're not compatible.

00:07:13.079 --> 00:07:14.280 position:27% line:89% align:start
Could be dicey.

00:07:14.313 --> 00:07:17.517 position:7% line:83% align:start
Who cares if it's dicey? She's
the one making the decision.

00:07:17.550 --> 00:07:19.085 position:41% line:89% align:start
Uh...

00:07:21.454 --> 00:07:22.789 position:27% line:89% align:start
[MAKOTO groans]

00:07:25.391 --> 00:07:26.659 position:41% line:83% align:start
[YURI]
Makoto.

00:07:26.692 --> 00:07:27.660 position:35% line:89% align:start
What's up?

00:07:27.693 --> 00:07:29.730 position:19% line:83% align:start
Decided on going with
arts or sciences yet?

00:07:29.763 --> 00:07:32.131 position:13% line:83% align:start
--Not yet. How 'bout you?
--Still thinking.

00:07:32.164 --> 00:07:33.533 position:5% line:89% align:start
Good. Then I'm not the only one.

00:07:33.566 --> 00:07:35.636 position:10% line:83% align:start
[YURI] It's a big decision.
We shouldn't rush it.

00:07:35.669 --> 00:07:37.671 position:16% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO] Yeah, who knows
how things'll turn out.

00:07:37.704 --> 00:07:40.506 position:21% line:83% align:start
[YURI] I'll be glad
when all this is over.

00:07:40.540 --> 00:07:42.475 position:38% line:83% align:start
[CHIAKI]
Hey, Makoto!

00:07:42.508 --> 00:07:44.343 position:21% line:83% align:start
How much longer you
gonna make us wait?

00:07:44.377 --> 00:07:46.345 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
You could always come and help!

00:07:46.379 --> 00:07:49.081 position:13% line:83% align:start
[CHIAKI] Ha, ha, ha. Yeah,
like that's ever gonna happen.

00:07:49.115 --> 00:07:50.416 position:35% line:83% align:start
[KOUSUKE]
Just hurry up, all right?

00:07:50.450 --> 00:07:51.785 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
Yeah, yeah.

00:07:54.688 --> 00:07:56.757 position:30% line:83% align:start
I wonder what
Chiaki's going into.

00:07:56.790 --> 00:07:59.125 position:24% line:83% align:start
Probably science.
He's not the book type.

00:07:59.158 --> 00:08:01.328 position:24% line:83% align:start
That's true. He is
amazing in math class.

00:08:01.361 --> 00:08:04.263 position:19% line:83% align:start
But that's it. Anyway,
why'd you bring up Chiaki?

00:08:04.298 --> 00:08:06.800 position:10% line:83% align:start
[STUDENT B] Hey, why haven't
the notebooks been put away?

00:08:06.833 --> 00:08:08.869 position:24% line:83% align:start
Who's supposed to
take them upstairs?

00:08:08.902 --> 00:08:11.338 position:27% line:83% align:start
--I don't know?
--You are!

00:08:11.371 --> 00:08:13.807 position:24% line:89% align:start
[MAKOTO grunting]

00:08:13.840 --> 00:08:16.276 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
What a hassle...

00:08:16.310 --> 00:08:26.320 position:27% line:89% align:start
[piano playing]

00:08:32.392 --> 00:08:34.895 position:27% line:89% align:start
[MAKOTO groans]

00:08:34.929 --> 00:08:36.463 position:44% line:89% align:start
Hm?

00:08:41.535 --> 00:08:44.538 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
"Time waits for no one."

00:08:44.571 --> 00:08:46.774 position:30% line:89% align:start
[door rattles]

00:08:46.808 --> 00:08:48.342 position:38% line:89% align:start
Huh...?

00:09:04.491 --> 00:09:10.598 position:35% line:89% align:start
[rattling]

00:09:26.381 --> 00:09:28.516 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
It's empty.

00:09:32.587 --> 00:09:34.489 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
That's weird.

00:09:34.522 --> 00:09:35.857 position:44% line:89% align:start
Hm.

00:09:42.697 --> 00:09:45.867 position:16% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO] It sounded like
someone was in here.

00:09:50.605 --> 00:09:51.973 position:41% line:89% align:start
Huh?!

00:09:52.007 --> 00:09:54.275 position:38% line:89% align:start
[grunts]

00:09:54.308 --> 00:09:55.643 position:41% line:89% align:start
Hm...

00:09:58.513 --> 00:10:01.683 position:16% line:89% align:start
The room's locked. Huh?!

00:10:06.287 --> 00:10:07.622 position:30% line:89% align:start
What is that?

00:10:19.868 --> 00:10:20.769 position:33% line:89% align:start
[clattering]

00:10:20.803 --> 00:10:21.502 position:38% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:10:21.536 --> 00:10:23.939 position:35% line:83% align:start
--[crash]
--[MAKOTO screams]

00:10:26.541 --> 00:10:27.876 position:38% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:10:29.778 --> 00:10:33.949 position:24% line:89% align:start
[MAKOTO screaming]

00:11:28.804 --> 00:11:32.041 position:35% line:89% align:start
[gasping]

00:11:37.747 --> 00:11:40.884 position:35% line:89% align:start
[groaning]

00:11:43.753 --> 00:11:47.456 position:24% line:89% align:start
[CHIAKI laughing]

00:11:47.489 --> 00:11:49.092 position:38% line:83% align:start
[CHIAKI]
A-Are you an idiot or what?!

00:11:49.125 --> 00:11:50.459 position:16% line:89% align:start
My stomach's killing me!

00:11:50.492 --> 00:11:51.561 position:35% line:83% align:start
[KOUSUKE]
C'mon. It's not that funny.

00:11:51.594 --> 00:11:53.563 position:21% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO] He's right.
You're laughing way too hard.

00:11:53.596 --> 00:11:55.532 position:38% line:83% align:start
[CHIAKI]
Get real, it's hilarious!

00:11:55.565 --> 00:11:56.699 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
It is not.

00:11:56.733 --> 00:11:58.568 position:13% line:83% align:start
[KOUSUKE] You wanna to my
dad's clinic for a CT scan?

00:11:58.601 --> 00:11:59.803 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
I'm fine, all right?

00:11:59.836 --> 00:12:02.337 position:10% line:83% align:start
[KOUSUKE] Okay, but, take it
easy. It could happen again.

00:12:02.371 --> 00:12:03.673 position:24% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO] It won't!
And if it does,

00:12:03.706 --> 00:12:05.008 position:10% line:89% align:start
I've got a serious problem.

00:12:05.041 --> 00:12:06.543 position:38% line:83% align:start
[CHIAKI]
He's got a point.

00:12:06.576 --> 00:12:08.411 position:10% line:83% align:start
It's not normal for someone
to just collapse.

00:12:08.444 --> 00:12:09.879 position:24% line:83% align:start
Hey, someone else
was in that room!

00:12:09.913 --> 00:12:10.647 position:24% line:89% align:start
What do you mean?

00:12:10.680 --> 00:12:11.714 position:35% line:89% align:start
Like, who?

00:12:11.748 --> 00:12:13.850 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
Gee... I wonder.

00:12:13.883 --> 00:12:16.653 position:16% line:83% align:start
[CHIAKI] You think I had
somethin' to do with it?!

00:12:16.686 --> 00:12:18.121 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
Maybe not.

00:12:18.154 --> 00:12:20.590 position:10% line:89% align:start
So I'm the bad guy suddenly?

00:12:22.458 --> 00:12:24.961 position:30% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO sighs]
Who could it have been?

00:12:27.764 --> 00:12:30.033 position:38% line:83% align:start
[CHIAKI]
Oh, man, it's hot out here!

00:12:30.066 --> 00:12:32.802 position:19% line:83% align:start
[KOUSUKE] Suck it up!
Summer vacation's almost here.

00:12:32.836 --> 00:12:34.671 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
Yeah! Summer vacation!

00:12:34.704 --> 00:12:36.573 position:21% line:83% align:start
Hey, the three of us
should go someplace!

00:12:36.606 --> 00:12:37.407 position:35% line:83% align:start
[KOUSUKE]
Like where?

00:12:37.440 --> 00:12:38.675 position:38% line:83% align:start
[CHIAKI]
Uh, how 'bout a night game?

00:12:38.708 --> 00:12:41.411 position:5% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO] We did that last month.
That's all you ever wanna do.

00:12:41.444 --> 00:12:42.146 position:38% line:83% align:start
[CHIAKI]
Any better ideas?

00:12:42.179 --> 00:12:43.479 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
What about the beach?

00:12:43.513 --> 00:12:44.480 position:24% line:83% align:start
[CHIAKI chuckles]
In this heat?

00:12:44.514 --> 00:12:46.549 position:16% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO] We could go to
a fireworks festival!

00:12:46.583 --> 00:12:48.018 position:13% line:89% align:start
And wear our best yukata.

00:12:48.052 --> 00:12:49.686 position:38% line:83% align:start
[CHIAKI]
Like I own one of those.

00:12:49.719 --> 00:12:51.621 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
Where do you wanna go, Kousuke?

00:12:52.522 --> 00:12:54.058 position:24% line:83% align:start
--To the library.
--[MAKOTO] What?!

00:12:54.091 --> 00:12:55.960 position:19% line:89% align:start
I'm hittin' the books!

00:12:55.993 --> 00:12:57.895 position:16% line:83% align:start
Your brain is gonna melt
if you keep cramming

00:12:57.928 --> 00:12:59.096 position:19% line:89% align:start
during this heat wave.

00:12:59.129 --> 00:13:00.898 position:21% line:83% align:start
You guys don't study
nearly enough.

00:13:00.931 --> 00:13:02.967 position:5% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO] It's not like I'm going
into pre-med or anything.

00:13:03.000 --> 00:13:04.835 position:24% line:83% align:start
What're you gonna
be after grad, then?

00:13:04.869 --> 00:13:06.603 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
Huh?

00:13:06.636 --> 00:13:08.906 position:19% line:89% align:start
Hmm... A hotel tycoon.

00:13:08.939 --> 00:13:09.640 position:35% line:83% align:start
[KOUSUKE]
Huh?!

00:13:09.673 --> 00:13:11.175 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
Or maybe an oil baron.

00:13:11.208 --> 00:13:15.545 position:19% line:83% align:start
Get real. It's nothin'
to joke about. Uh!

00:13:15.579 --> 00:13:19.116 position:21% line:83% align:start
Hey... What are you
gonna do, Chiaki?

00:13:19.149 --> 00:13:21.051 position:38% line:89% align:start
Who, me?

00:13:21.085 --> 00:13:23.754 position:38% line:89% align:start
I dunno.

00:13:23.787 --> 00:13:26.957 position:41% line:83% align:start
--Ow!
--[laughing]

00:13:26.991 --> 00:13:30.060 position:13% line:83% align:start
You two gotta start takin'
life more seriously.

00:13:30.094 --> 00:13:31.762 position:30% line:89% align:start
Goin' already?

00:13:31.795 --> 00:13:33.097 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
Yep. Just remembered something

00:13:33.130 --> 00:13:34.231 position:27% line:83% align:start
that mom wanted
me to do for her.

00:13:34.265 --> 00:13:37.001 position:5% line:83% align:start
Huh? But... No, no, no, no, no.
Don't be a party pooper.

00:13:37.034 --> 00:13:38.469 position:5% line:89% align:start
You're leavin' me with the nerd!

00:13:38.502 --> 00:13:40.204 position:27% line:89% align:start
Guess so. Later!

00:13:40.237 --> 00:13:43.007 position:38% line:83% align:start
[CHIAKI]
C'mon, Mako. You're heartless.

00:13:44.074 --> 00:13:44.742 position:27% line:89% align:start
Let's get going.

00:13:44.775 --> 00:13:46.543 position:7% line:89% align:start
But the elves are coming out!

00:13:46.577 --> 00:13:48.512 position:27% line:89% align:start
Good heavens...

00:13:49.546 --> 00:13:50.348 position:41% line:89% align:start
Huh?!

00:13:50.382 --> 00:13:53.118 position:27% line:83% align:start
Whoa! Hey! Watch
where you're going!

00:13:53.151 --> 00:13:54.885 position:35% line:89% align:start
I'm sorry!

00:13:54.919 --> 00:13:59.690 position:21% line:89% align:start
[clock chime plays]

00:13:59.723 --> 00:14:01.458 position:16% line:89% align:start
[crossing gates ringing]

00:14:01.492 --> 00:14:02.493 position:38% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:14:04.195 --> 00:14:07.098 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
If today was like...

00:14:07.132 --> 00:14:09.500 position:24% line:83% align:start
If today was like
any other day...

00:14:09.533 --> 00:14:12.003 position:19% line:83% align:start
...there wouldn't have
been any problems.

00:14:12.037 --> 00:14:13.570 position:41% line:89% align:start
But...

00:14:17.574 --> 00:14:18.742 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
I'd forgotten.

00:14:18.776 --> 00:14:22.013 position:24% line:83% align:start
Today was supposed
to be my worst day ever.

00:14:24.215 --> 00:14:25.750 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
Ah!

00:14:27.018 --> 00:14:28.186 position:24% line:89% align:start
[MAKOTO whimpers]

00:14:29.187 --> 00:14:32.257 position:10% line:89% align:start
[MAKOTO groaning, screaming]

00:14:32.290 --> 00:14:33.490 position:38% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:14:34.092 --> 00:14:37.062 position:24% line:89% align:start
[MAKOTO shrieking]

00:14:38.697 --> 00:14:43.702 position:30% line:83% align:start
--[bell tolls]
--[CROWD murmurs]

00:14:51.142 --> 00:14:52.510 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
You're probably thinking

00:14:52.544 --> 00:14:54.012 position:7% line:89% align:start
that this can't be happening,

00:14:54.045 --> 00:14:55.880 position:19% line:89% align:start
but I'm going to die.

00:14:55.914 --> 00:14:58.683 position:21% line:89% align:start
This is my last day.

00:14:58.717 --> 00:15:00.051 position:24% line:83% align:start
If I knew this was
going to happen,

00:15:00.085 --> 00:15:02.554 position:7% line:89% align:start
I would've gotten up earlier.

00:15:02.587 --> 00:15:06.024 position:13% line:83% align:start
I wouldn't have slept in,
and I wouldn't have been late.

00:15:06.057 --> 00:15:07.826 position:19% line:83% align:start
I would've fried that
tempura better.

00:15:07.859 --> 00:15:10.895 position:7% line:83% align:start
And that stupid boy at school
wouldn't've been thrown into me.

00:15:10.929 --> 00:15:15.267 position:19% line:83% align:start
I thought today... was
supposed to be a "Nice Day."

00:15:26.678 --> 00:15:28.280 position:24% line:89% align:start
[MAKOTO groaning]

00:15:28.314 --> 00:15:29.348 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
Ow...

00:15:29.382 --> 00:15:32.318 position:16% line:83% align:start
[WOMAN B] Hey! Will you
watch where you're going?!

00:15:32.351 --> 00:15:32.985 position:38% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:15:33.019 --> 00:15:34.686 position:10% line:89% align:start
So, you gonna say somthing?!

00:15:34.719 --> 00:15:37.256 position:16% line:83% align:start
The very least you could
do is give an apology!

00:15:38.656 --> 00:15:40.592 position:16% line:89% align:start
Sorry! I'm really sorry.

00:15:40.625 --> 00:15:41.793 position:35% line:83% align:start
[WOMAN B]
Do you even know why

00:15:41.827 --> 00:15:43.162 position:21% line:83% align:start
you have eyes in the
front of your head?!

00:15:43.195 --> 00:15:45.831 position:16% line:83% align:start
So you can see what's in
front of you! You got that?!

00:15:45.865 --> 00:15:48.034 position:24% line:83% align:start
Yes, I'll try and
be more careful.

00:15:48.067 --> 00:15:51.203 position:24% line:83% align:start
Good grief, young
kids these days...!

00:15:51.237 --> 00:15:53.172 position:21% line:83% align:start
Mom, look! The elves
are coming out!

00:15:53.205 --> 00:15:54.340 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:15:54.373 --> 00:15:56.608 position:35% line:83% align:start
Oh, dear.
Is it that time already?

00:15:56.642 --> 00:15:57.977 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:16:06.919 --> 00:16:08.854 position:24% line:89% align:start
What? It can't be.

00:16:08.888 --> 00:16:10.756 position:16% line:89% align:start
[crossing gates ringing]

00:16:12.825 --> 00:16:14.160 position:33% line:89% align:start
Impossible!

00:16:31.911 --> 00:16:33.979 position:30% line:89% align:start
[phone rings]

00:16:34.013 --> 00:16:35.348 position:24% line:83% align:start
[MUSEUM EMPLOYEE]
Hello?

00:16:37.184 --> 00:16:38.751 position:24% line:83% align:start
[MUSEUM EMPLOYEE]
Miss Yoshiyama?

00:16:38.784 --> 00:16:40.120 position:44% line:89% align:start
Uh?

00:16:55.302 --> 00:16:56.336 position:27% line:89% align:start
[MAKOTO groans]

00:16:56.369 --> 00:16:57.204 position:13% line:89% align:start
[SECURITY GUARD chuckles]

00:16:57.237 --> 00:16:59.339 position:30% line:83% align:start
Take it easy.
She'll be right down.

00:16:59.372 --> 00:17:00.773 position:38% line:83% align:start
[KAZUKO]
Makoto!

00:17:00.806 --> 00:17:02.976 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
Auntie!

00:17:03.009 --> 00:17:04.344 position:30% line:89% align:start
Auntie Witch!

00:17:07.247 --> 00:17:10.283 position:19% line:83% align:start
Tell me, am I alive?!
I am alive, aren't I?!

00:17:10.317 --> 00:17:13.854 position:16% line:83% align:start
There's-There's nothing
wrong with me, is there?

00:17:13.887 --> 00:17:16.056 position:38% line:83% align:start
[KAZUKO]
Hmm...

00:17:16.089 --> 00:17:18.892 position:27% line:83% align:start
Your bangs look
a little strange.

00:17:19.926 --> 00:17:22.262 position:21% line:83% align:start
What you experienced
was a time leap.

00:17:22.295 --> 00:17:23.997 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
Time leap?!

00:17:24.030 --> 00:17:26.166 position:16% line:83% align:start
You were about to be hit
by a train, right?

00:17:26.199 --> 00:17:27.134 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
Yeah.

00:17:27.167 --> 00:17:28.902 position:21% line:83% align:start
Shortly after being
thrown from your bike?

00:17:28.935 --> 00:17:30.170 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
Yeah!

00:17:30.203 --> 00:17:32.339 position:5% line:83% align:start
And then when you came to, you'd
gone back a few minutes in time.

00:17:32.372 --> 00:17:33.140 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
Exactly!

00:17:33.173 --> 00:17:35.175 position:27% line:83% align:start
That's what you
call a time leap.

00:17:35.208 --> 00:17:37.811 position:24% line:83% align:start
You see, time can
never be reversed.

00:17:37.844 --> 00:17:38.945 position:24% line:89% align:start
Then how did I...

00:17:38.979 --> 00:17:40.947 position:38% line:83% align:start
[KAZUKO]
Time itself doesn't go back.

00:17:40.981 --> 00:17:43.884 position:24% line:83% align:start
So it was you that
went back in time.

00:17:43.917 --> 00:17:45.886 position:27% line:83% align:start
In other words,
you leapt through time

00:17:45.919 --> 00:17:48.722 position:13% line:89% align:start
and returned to the past.

00:17:48.755 --> 00:17:50.056 position:30% line:89% align:start
Are you sure?

00:17:50.090 --> 00:17:53.294 position:16% line:83% align:start
[KAZUKO] Yes. Actually,
it's not that unusual.

00:17:53.327 --> 00:17:57.365 position:19% line:83% align:start
It happens to a lot of
girls around your age.

00:17:57.398 --> 00:18:00.000 position:24% line:83% align:start
No way. Trust me.
It never happens.

00:18:00.033 --> 00:18:01.835 position:24% line:89% align:start
It happened to me.

00:18:01.868 --> 00:18:03.204 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
What?! Are you serious?

00:18:03.237 --> 00:18:06.207 position:16% line:83% align:start
Yes. All right, say you
sleep in on a Sunday morning.

00:18:06.307 --> 00:18:07.908 position:19% line:89% align:start
And... And you think,

00:18:07.941 --> 00:18:12.180 position:13% line:83% align:start
"I don't wanna do anything
today." Sound familiar?

00:18:12.213 --> 00:18:14.714 position:13% line:83% align:start
Then, before you know it,
it's already evening.

00:18:14.748 --> 00:18:16.150 position:13% line:89% align:start
It comes as quite a shock.

00:18:16.184 --> 00:18:19.487 position:10% line:83% align:start
You're like, "What happened
to my precious Sunday?"

00:18:19.520 --> 00:18:21.355 position:21% line:83% align:start
I wish you'd take me
more seriously,

00:18:21.389 --> 00:18:22.990 position:10% line:89% align:start
I'm not joking around here.

00:18:23.024 --> 00:18:25.927 position:24% line:83% align:start
[KAZUKO] Anyway...
It's a good thing you're alive.

00:18:25.960 --> 00:18:28.129 position:10% line:89% align:start
How 'bout cheering up a bit?

00:18:28.162 --> 00:18:31.799 position:16% line:89% align:start
[MAKOTO chuckles weakly]

00:18:31.832 --> 00:18:34.001 position:24% line:89% align:start
[KAZUKO chuckles]

00:18:37.538 --> 00:18:38.773 position:38% line:89% align:start
Miyuki?

00:18:38.806 --> 00:18:40.341 position:38% line:89% align:start
Uh-huh?

00:18:40.374 --> 00:18:43.144 position:10% line:83% align:start
--Would you mind helping me?
--All right.

00:18:47.048 --> 00:18:48.416 position:38% line:83% align:start
[KAZUKO]
Show me how you did it.

00:18:48.449 --> 00:18:49.417 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
I can't!

00:18:49.450 --> 00:18:51.352 position:16% line:83% align:start
[KAZUKO] I'm sure if you
get the technique down,

00:18:51.385 --> 00:18:52.954 position:7% line:89% align:start
you'll be able to do it again.

00:18:52.987 --> 00:18:54.922 position:21% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO] I'm telling
you it's not possible!

00:19:01.195 --> 00:19:03.864 position:21% line:83% align:start
[KAZUKO] But you did
actually fly through the air,

00:19:03.898 --> 00:19:05.233 position:30% line:89% align:start
right, Makoto?

00:19:15.243 --> 00:19:17.211 position:33% line:83% align:start
--Like this?
--Yeah. Tear that off.

00:19:17.246 --> 00:19:18.779 position:38% line:89% align:start
[crash]

00:19:20.549 --> 00:19:22.817 position:7% line:89% align:start
What was that? An earthquake?

00:19:22.850 --> 00:19:25.853 position:24% line:89% align:start
[MAKOTO groaning]

00:19:39.334 --> 00:19:40.868 position:38% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:19:41.503 --> 00:19:43.438 position:19% line:89% align:start
No, Sis! Don't do it!

00:19:43.472 --> 00:19:44.039 position:30% line:89% align:start
[MAKOTO yelps]

00:19:44.072 --> 00:19:46.108 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MIYUKI]
I'm begging you!

00:19:46.141 --> 00:19:48.076 position:33% line:89% align:start
[BOTH grunt]

00:19:48.110 --> 00:19:49.810 position:7% line:89% align:start
I'm sorry! Please forgive me!

00:19:49.845 --> 00:19:51.046 position:19% line:89% align:start
This is all my fault!

00:19:51.079 --> 00:19:54.283 position:7% line:83% align:start
Why are you doing this? Was it
because I ate your pudding?!

00:19:54.316 --> 00:19:55.951 position:19% line:89% align:start
Uh. What do you mean?

00:19:55.984 --> 00:19:57.519 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MIYUKI]
I don't want you to die, Sis!

00:19:57.552 --> 00:19:59.221 position:21% line:89% align:start
Nobody's gonna die!

00:19:59.254 --> 00:20:01.356 position:10% line:83% align:start
--Where are you going, then?
--To the store!

00:20:01.390 --> 00:20:03.425 position:13% line:83% align:start
If it's pudding you want,
I can go buy it.

00:20:03.458 --> 00:20:05.193 position:7% line:89% align:start
Don't worry about it, I'll go.

00:20:05.227 --> 00:20:07.429 position:16% line:83% align:start
--[MIYUKI] Are you mad?
--[MAKOTO] No, I'm not mad.

00:20:07.462 --> 00:20:08.964 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MIYUKI]
You positive?

00:20:08.997 --> 00:20:11.099 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
I'm not mad, okay?

00:20:11.133 --> 00:20:12.467 position:38% line:89% align:start
[sighs]

00:20:24.447 --> 00:20:25.981 position:38% line:83% align:start
[BOY A]
Watch this!

00:20:28.050 --> 00:20:30.420 position:38% line:83% align:start
[BOY B]
Whoa! Cool!

00:20:30.453 --> 00:20:33.523 position:16% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO] There's no way.
How can you leap back in time?

00:20:33.556 --> 00:20:36.224 position:7% line:89% align:start
It's definitely not possible.

00:20:37.427 --> 00:20:38.561 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
No chance.

00:20:38.594 --> 00:20:41.129 position:24% line:83% align:start
At least it's not
something that I can do.

00:20:50.673 --> 00:20:56.446 position:19% line:83% align:start
[RUNNERS] Left! Right!
Left! Right! Left! Right!

00:21:04.454 --> 00:21:12.028 position:27% line:89% align:start
[MAKOTO panting]

00:21:16.032 --> 00:21:17.533 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
Here...

00:21:19.035 --> 00:21:22.438 position:44% line:89% align:start
Go!

00:21:40.691 --> 00:21:41.991 position:38% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:21:43.727 --> 00:21:46.929 position:35% line:89% align:start
[screams]

00:21:49.198 --> 00:21:51.100 position:24% line:89% align:start
[MAKOTO screaming]

00:21:59.476 --> 00:22:00.277 position:30% line:89% align:start
[MAKOTO yelps]

00:22:00.310 --> 00:22:02.413 position:27% line:89% align:start
[MAKOTO groans]

00:22:02.446 --> 00:22:04.213 position:41% line:89% align:start
Ow...!

00:22:04.248 --> 00:22:05.549 position:41% line:89% align:start
Huh?!

00:22:05.582 --> 00:22:08.452 position:16% line:89% align:start
What the...? Where am I?

00:22:11.755 --> 00:22:14.691 position:30% line:89% align:start
Oh, I'm home.

00:22:16.360 --> 00:22:19.530 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
Pudding?

00:22:19.563 --> 00:22:22.533 position:7% line:89% align:start
My pudding... It's still here.

00:22:28.005 --> 00:22:29.640 position:38% line:89% align:start
[sighs]

