00:38:34.483 --> 00:38:36.017 position:44% line:89% align:start
I...

00:38:38.019 --> 00:38:39.921 position:38% line:83% align:start
[CHIAKI]
What's the matter?

00:38:42.190 --> 00:38:44.125 position:38% line:83% align:start
[TAKASE]
Konno, you jerk!

00:38:44.225 --> 00:38:45.093 position:41% line:89% align:start
Huh?!

00:38:45.126 --> 00:38:46.961 position:24% line:83% align:start
Why did you ask me
to fry that tempura

00:38:46.995 --> 00:38:48.230 position:19% line:83% align:start
in the Home Ec. class
the other day?!

00:38:48.264 --> 00:38:49.465 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
Uh, well, I never thought

00:38:49.498 --> 00:38:50.999 position:21% line:83% align:start
something like that
would happen!

00:38:51.032 --> 00:38:52.668 position:7% line:89% align:start
This is all your fault, idiot!

00:38:52.701 --> 00:38:56.472 position:7% line:83% align:start
Who are you calling an idiot?!
Keep it up and I'll throw this!

00:38:56.505 --> 00:38:57.373 position:24% line:89% align:start
No, don't, Chiaki.

00:38:57.406 --> 00:38:59.375 position:24% line:89% align:start
Yeah? I dare you!

00:38:59.408 --> 00:39:00.609 position:27% line:89% align:start
[TAKASE grunts]

00:39:00.643 --> 00:39:02.144 position:27% line:89% align:start
[STUDENTS laugh]

00:39:02.178 --> 00:39:05.114 position:38% line:83% align:start
[CHIAKI]
Ohh. I didn't mean to do that.

00:39:05.147 --> 00:39:07.249 position:38% line:83% align:start
[TAKASE]
Stupid!

00:39:07.283 --> 00:39:09.018 position:38% line:83% align:start
[CHIAKI]
That guy's pretty rude.

00:39:09.051 --> 00:39:10.719 position:21% line:83% align:start
Goin' around calling
everyone names.

00:39:10.753 --> 00:39:13.622 position:13% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO] So? You're always
calling me an idiot.

00:39:13.656 --> 00:39:16.525 position:16% line:83% align:start
[CHIAKI] Heh, heh. Yeah,
but I say it out of love.

00:39:20.229 --> 00:39:22.131 position:38% line:83% align:start
[CHIAKI]
C'mon, where's your comeback?

00:39:22.164 --> 00:39:23.666 position:24% line:83% align:start
You're leaving me
in the cold here.

00:39:23.699 --> 00:39:26.268 position:19% line:83% align:start
Uh. She acting weird,
don't you think, Hayakawa?

00:39:26.302 --> 00:39:28.471 position:41% line:83% align:start
[YURI]
Oh, uh... yes, indeed.

00:39:28.504 --> 00:39:29.605 position:38% line:83% align:start
[CHIAKI]
Why the stiff talk?

00:39:29.638 --> 00:39:30.707 position:38% line:83% align:start
[YURI]
Sorry, it's just that

00:39:30.740 --> 00:39:33.142 position:21% line:83% align:start
I haven't spoken to
you much before.

00:40:13.148 --> 00:40:14.518 position:38% line:83% align:start
[CHIAKI]
Makoto!

00:40:18.522 --> 00:40:19.723 position:35% line:83% align:start
[KOUSUKE]
She's not here.

00:40:19.756 --> 00:40:21.491 position:7% line:89% align:start
But she always meets us here.

00:40:21.525 --> 00:40:23.126 position:21% line:83% align:start
--Somethin' happen?
--Huh?

00:40:23.159 --> 00:40:25.395 position:16% line:89% align:start
No! No, nothin' at all!

00:40:25.428 --> 00:40:27.731 position:13% line:83% align:start
You must've said somethin'
that pissed her off.

00:40:27.764 --> 00:40:29.266 position:21% line:83% align:start
You better not have
said she has big feet.

00:40:29.299 --> 00:40:30.567 position:7% line:89% align:start
You know she's self-conscious.

00:40:30.600 --> 00:40:33.303 position:38% line:83% align:start
[CHIAKI]
I didn't say anything!

00:40:34.104 --> 00:40:35.438 position:35% line:89% align:start
I didn't!

00:40:38.408 --> 00:40:40.176 position:19% line:89% align:start
I don't think I did...

00:40:41.144 --> 00:40:42.078 position:44% line:89% align:start
Uh?

00:40:42.112 --> 00:40:43.446 position:38% line:89% align:start
[grunts]

00:40:44.815 --> 00:40:46.516 position:35% line:83% align:start
[KOUSUKE]
Toss it back!

00:40:49.854 --> 00:40:52.088 position:24% line:83% align:start
I can't throw good
when I'm thinking.

00:40:56.159 --> 00:40:59.362 position:30% line:83% align:start
It's no use...
I just don't get it!

00:41:13.209 --> 00:41:15.378 position:27% line:89% align:start
[phone vibrates]

00:41:15.412 --> 00:41:18.214 position:27% line:89% align:start
[MAKOTO groans]

00:41:18.248 --> 00:41:20.384 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
Oh, it's Yuri.

00:41:20.418 --> 00:41:23.654 position:16% line:83% align:start
"Something really great
happened today!"

00:41:23.688 --> 00:41:25.856 position:30% line:89% align:start
I wonder what.

00:41:30.428 --> 00:41:35.433 position:30% line:89% align:start
[dog barking]

00:41:37.268 --> 00:41:41.472 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MIYUKI]
Hello? Oh, hi. Yeah. Hang on.

00:41:41.505 --> 00:41:44.208 position:16% line:89% align:start
Yeah... Uh-huh, yeah...

00:41:52.717 --> 00:41:55.419 position:13% line:89% align:start
Wonder what her news was?

00:41:55.453 --> 00:41:57.855 position:33% line:89% align:start
[bell rings]

00:41:57.888 --> 00:42:01.225 position:10% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO] Hurry up, let's go!
Before they sell out!

00:42:01.258 --> 00:42:04.295 position:13% line:83% align:start
Actually, I'm not feeling
all that well today.

00:42:04.328 --> 00:42:05.796 position:21% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO] Wanna go to
the nurse's office?

00:42:05.830 --> 00:42:08.733 position:16% line:83% align:start
Oh! U-Uh. N-No, thanks!
I'll be fine.

00:42:31.455 --> 00:42:33.959 position:13% line:83% align:start
[STUDENT F] C'mon, hurry,
this is gonna be good.

00:42:33.992 --> 00:42:36.662 position:33% line:83% align:start
[STUDENT G]
C'mon! C'mon, man!

00:42:36.695 --> 00:42:38.429 position:10% line:83% align:start
--[STUDENT H] Did you hear?!
--[STUDENT I] This way!

00:42:38.463 --> 00:42:42.233 position:19% line:89% align:start
[STUDENTS chattering]

00:42:45.971 --> 00:42:47.204 position:38% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:42:47.238 --> 00:42:50.542 position:24% line:89% align:start
[BULLIES groaning]

00:42:50.575 --> 00:42:53.378 position:38% line:83% align:start
[BULLY]
Knock it off, Takase! Ah!

00:42:53.412 --> 00:42:57.282 position:5% line:83% align:start
Why should I listen to you?! You
didn't stop when I asked you to!

00:42:57.315 --> 00:42:59.484 position:24% line:83% align:start
[BULLY] All right!
I admit, we were wrong!

00:42:59.518 --> 00:43:01.620 position:5% line:83% align:start
[TAKASE] Then you shouldn't have
done it to me to begin with!

00:43:01.653 --> 00:43:03.455 position:10% line:83% align:start
[STUDENT J] Jeez. That guy's
lost it. Anyone call a teacher?

00:43:03.488 --> 00:43:05.357 position:33% line:83% align:start
[STUDENT K]
Come and see this.

00:43:05.390 --> 00:43:07.325 position:21% line:89% align:start
Put it down, Takase!

00:43:07.359 --> 00:43:08.727 position:38% line:89% align:start
Takase!

00:43:12.931 --> 00:43:13.965 position:41% line:89% align:start
Konno!

00:43:13.999 --> 00:43:14.833 position:38% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:43:14.866 --> 00:43:17.369 position:38% line:83% align:start
[TAKASE]
Did you just give me an order?!

00:43:17.402 --> 00:43:19.304 position:16% line:89% align:start
No, it wasn't like that!

00:43:19.337 --> 00:43:21.406 position:30% line:89% align:start
Yes, you did!

00:43:21.440 --> 00:43:24.443 position:16% line:83% align:start
--[STUDENTS gasp, yell]
--[MAKOTO yelps]

00:43:24.476 --> 00:43:25.510 position:41% line:89% align:start
Huh?!

00:43:25.544 --> 00:43:27.546 position:35% line:89% align:start
[grunting]

00:43:27.579 --> 00:43:30.415 position:16% line:83% align:start
[TAKASE] Why?! Damn it!
Why won't it work?

00:43:32.484 --> 00:43:33.452 position:38% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:43:33.485 --> 00:43:34.453 position:24% line:83% align:start
--[MAKOTO screams]
--[STUDENTS gasp, scream]

00:43:34.486 --> 00:43:36.989 position:19% line:83% align:start
--[STUDENTS murmuring]
--Don't do it, Takase!

00:43:37.023 --> 00:43:40.325 position:21% line:83% align:start
--[TAKASE grunting]
--[MAKOTO gasps]

00:43:40.358 --> 00:43:41.794 position:38% line:89% align:start
Takase!

00:43:41.828 --> 00:43:44.764 position:35% line:89% align:start
[yelling]

00:43:44.797 --> 00:43:46.799 position:16% line:89% align:start
[STUDENTS gasp, scream]

00:43:48.668 --> 00:43:50.002 position:24% line:89% align:start
[MAKOTO whimpers]

00:43:53.305 --> 00:43:53.906 position:38% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:43:53.940 --> 00:43:55.474 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
Chiaki!

00:43:57.009 --> 00:43:58.544 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
Chiaki!

00:44:03.015 --> 00:44:04.917 position:27% line:89% align:start
[MAKOTO grunts]

00:44:04.951 --> 00:44:08.020 position:19% line:89% align:start
[MAKOTO, CHIAKI grunt]

00:44:08.054 --> 00:44:10.288 position:41% line:83% align:start
[YURI]
Ahh!

00:44:10.322 --> 00:44:12.725 position:13% line:83% align:start
--[STUDENTS murmur, gasp]
--[MAKOTO gasps]

00:44:12.759 --> 00:44:14.060 position:10% line:83% align:start
--[STUDENT L] Are you okay?!
--[STUDENT M] Yuri!

00:44:14.093 --> 00:44:15.428 position:33% line:83% align:start
[STUDENT N]
That hit her big time!

00:44:15.461 --> 00:44:16.429 position:33% line:83% align:start
[STUDENT O]
What grade's she in?

00:44:16.462 --> 00:44:17.964 position:16% line:89% align:start
Someone call a teacher!

00:44:17.997 --> 00:44:21.567 position:10% line:83% align:start
[TAKASE] It wasn't my fault!
It wasn't... I-I swear!

00:44:21.601 --> 00:44:24.670 position:21% line:89% align:start
[STUDENTS murmuring]

00:44:32.979 --> 00:44:36.616 position:30% line:89% align:start
[YURI sobbing]

00:44:36.649 --> 00:44:39.952 position:19% line:83% align:start
[NURSE] Now don't cry.
It's not that bad.

00:44:39.986 --> 00:44:41.954 position:41% line:83% align:start
[YURI]
What if it leaves a scar...?

00:44:43.356 --> 00:44:47.060 position:33% line:83% align:start
If it does,
I'll deal with it somehow.

00:44:47.094 --> 00:44:48.628 position:13% line:89% align:start
How are you gonna do that?

00:44:48.661 --> 00:44:51.330 position:19% line:89% align:start
I'll handle it, okay?

00:45:04.044 --> 00:45:05.746 position:38% line:83% align:start
[NURSE]
No boys in here, please.

00:45:05.779 --> 00:45:07.446 position:38% line:83% align:start
[CHIAKI]
Does it hurt?

00:45:07.480 --> 00:45:08.649 position:41% line:83% align:start
[YURI]
Yeah.

00:45:08.682 --> 00:45:10.516 position:19% line:83% align:start
--[CHIAKI] Let's see.
--[YURI] No.

00:45:10.550 --> 00:45:11.885 position:38% line:83% align:start
[CHIAKI]
Come on.

00:45:13.587 --> 00:45:14.922 position:41% line:83% align:start
[YURI]
Thanks.

00:45:22.896 --> 00:45:24.598 position:38% line:83% align:start
[CHIAKI]
I'm sorry, seriously!

00:45:24.631 --> 00:45:25.899 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
Huh?! But, why?!

00:45:25.933 --> 00:45:28.535 position:38% line:83% align:start
[CHIAKI]
I said I'm sorry, really!

00:45:28.569 --> 00:45:30.037 position:19% line:83% align:start
Ugh. Give me a break.
I mean,

00:45:30.070 --> 00:45:32.573 position:10% line:83% align:start
who takes a girl to a night
game on their first date?

00:45:32.606 --> 00:45:35.509 position:10% line:83% align:start
Yeah! I thought you said the
three of us were going together!

00:45:35.542 --> 00:45:37.945 position:5% line:89% align:start
I was looking forward to it! Uh!

00:45:37.978 --> 00:45:40.113 position:24% line:83% align:start
How many times do
I have to say sorry?

00:45:40.147 --> 00:45:42.883 position:19% line:83% align:start
Hayakawa said a night
game would work for her.

00:45:42.916 --> 00:45:45.018 position:21% line:89% align:start
You gonna date her?

00:45:45.052 --> 00:45:46.520 position:16% line:83% align:start
--[CHIAKI] You know it!
--[MAKOTO] Ah...

00:45:46.553 --> 00:45:48.722 position:38% line:89% align:start
[grunts]

00:45:48.755 --> 00:45:49.990 position:35% line:83% align:start
[KOUSUKE]
Oh. You all right?

00:45:50.023 --> 00:45:50.858 position:33% line:89% align:start
Ya serious?

00:45:50.891 --> 00:45:52.693 position:38% line:83% align:start
[CHIAKI]
Yeah, somethin' wrong with that?

00:45:54.962 --> 00:45:57.965 position:16% line:83% align:start
[CHIAKI] Well, what can
I say? Yuri gets me.

00:45:57.998 --> 00:45:59.733 position:19% line:89% align:start
You know what I mean?

00:45:59.766 --> 00:46:02.436 position:19% line:89% align:start
How nice for you! Uh!

00:46:02.469 --> 00:46:07.608 position:5% line:83% align:start
[CHIAKI grunts] Jeez! You idiot!
How 'bout aiming first?!

00:46:11.012 --> 00:46:13.915 position:30% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO'S DAD]
I'm home!

00:46:13.948 --> 00:46:17.819 position:10% line:83% align:start
--Ah. Huh? Where's the rice?
--I'm making some more.

00:46:17.852 --> 00:46:18.652 position:44% line:89% align:start
Why?

00:46:18.685 --> 00:46:21.055 position:21% line:83% align:start
Makoto ate the whole
batch herself.

00:46:21.089 --> 00:46:22.623 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
Aww!

00:46:22.656 --> 00:46:23.825 position:19% line:89% align:start
What's wrong with him?

00:46:23.858 --> 00:46:28.129 position:13% line:83% align:start
First he says he likes me,
and now he's going out with her?

00:46:32.700 --> 00:46:37.939 position:24% line:89% align:start
[MAKOTO groaning]

00:46:37.972 --> 00:46:39.007 position:38% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:46:39.040 --> 00:46:43.177 position:35% line:89% align:start
[panting]

00:46:43.211 --> 00:46:45.647 position:24% line:89% align:start
I almost drowned!

00:46:45.680 --> 00:46:46.814 position:41% line:89% align:start
Huh?!

00:46:46.848 --> 00:46:48.783 position:33% line:89% align:start
Uh... huh...

00:46:50.652 --> 00:46:55.456 position:21% line:89% align:start
What is this thing?

00:46:55.490 --> 00:46:57.058 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
Ninety?

00:47:13.242 --> 00:47:14.809 position:35% line:83% align:start
[KOUSUKE]
Hey, Makoto!

00:47:14.842 --> 00:47:15.710 position:27% line:89% align:start
[MAKOTO grunts]

00:47:15.743 --> 00:47:18.079 position:21% line:83% align:start
--[KOUSUKE chuckles]
--[MAKOTO] Let go!

00:47:18.113 --> 00:47:19.948 position:38% line:83% align:start
[SEKIMI]
I think we lost this one.

00:47:19.981 --> 00:47:22.051 position:13% line:83% align:start
She's putting us to shame,
that's for sure.

00:47:22.084 --> 00:47:23.918 position:10% line:89% align:start
The world is full of deceit.

00:47:23.952 --> 00:47:25.486 position:38% line:89% align:start
[sighs]

00:47:29.291 --> 00:47:31.893 position:21% line:83% align:start
[KOUSUKE] Sucks not
having Chiaki here. Uh!

00:47:31.926 --> 00:47:33.861 position:24% line:83% align:start
Let's make sure we
get him here tomorrow.

00:47:33.895 --> 00:47:35.931 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
That wouldn't be fair to Yuri.

00:47:35.965 --> 00:47:38.968 position:13% line:83% align:start
[KOUSUKE sighs] How 'bout
I say that you miss him?

00:47:39.001 --> 00:47:40.535 position:21% line:89% align:start
Bet he'd come then.

00:47:40.568 --> 00:47:43.238 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
Who said I miss him?!

00:47:43.272 --> 00:47:45.975 position:21% line:83% align:start
Ah, please, he only
went with Hayakawa

00:47:46.008 --> 00:47:47.042 position:10% line:89% align:start
'cause you turned him down.

00:47:47.076 --> 00:47:48.509 position:27% line:89% align:start
What! I did not.

00:47:48.543 --> 00:47:49.577 position:35% line:83% align:start
[KOUSUKE]
Really?

00:47:49.610 --> 00:47:51.246 position:7% line:89% align:start
What's that supposed to mean?!

00:47:52.815 --> 00:47:54.049 position:30% line:89% align:start
Oh, brother...

00:47:54.083 --> 00:47:57.720 position:5% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO] So what's the deal with
you? Why don't you find a girl?

00:47:57.753 --> 00:47:59.922 position:10% line:83% align:start
'Cause if I did start goin'
out with someone...

00:47:59.955 --> 00:48:02.291 position:10% line:89% align:start
...then you'd end up alone.

00:48:02.324 --> 00:48:03.859 position:41% line:89% align:start
Huh?!

00:48:07.863 --> 00:48:10.699 position:13% line:83% align:start
[KAZUKO] I thought you had
a thing for Kousuke?

00:48:10.733 --> 00:48:12.134 position:7% line:89% align:start
He's the one who always helps

00:48:12.167 --> 00:48:15.104 position:24% line:83% align:start
when you're having
problems, right?

00:48:15.137 --> 00:48:17.740 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
Kousuke's there for everyone.

00:48:17.773 --> 00:48:19.208 position:38% line:83% align:start
[KAZUKO]
Why don't you go out with him?

00:48:19.241 --> 00:48:20.909 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
Why would you even suggest that?

00:48:20.943 --> 00:48:22.945 position:10% line:83% align:start
[KAZUKO] Like I said before,
if it doesn't work out,

00:48:22.978 --> 00:48:24.947 position:19% line:83% align:start
you can always go back
to how it was.

00:48:24.980 --> 00:48:27.016 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
No way. I would never do it.

00:48:27.049 --> 00:48:27.816 position:38% line:83% align:start
[KAZUKO]
Why is that?

00:48:27.850 --> 00:48:28.917 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
'Cause it'd be like toying

00:48:28.951 --> 00:48:30.119 position:10% line:89% align:start
with a person's feelings...

00:48:30.152 --> 00:48:31.553 position:38% line:83% align:start
[KAZUKO]
And you couldn't possibly do

00:48:31.587 --> 00:48:32.121 position:19% line:89% align:start
such a terrible thing?

00:48:32.154 --> 00:48:33.088 position:44% line:89% align:start
Uh?

00:48:33.122 --> 00:48:34.723 position:16% line:83% align:start
Since you started going
back into the past,

00:48:34.757 --> 00:48:36.259 position:21% line:83% align:start
you haven't exactly
shown restraint.

00:48:36.292 --> 00:48:38.827 position:13% line:83% align:start
You've played all sorts of
mind games with people.

00:48:38.861 --> 00:48:41.264 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
What? Is that how you see it?

00:48:41.297 --> 00:48:43.299 position:30% line:89% align:start
More or less.

00:48:45.135 --> 00:48:46.102 position:30% line:89% align:start
She's a witch.

00:48:46.136 --> 00:48:49.571 position:19% line:83% align:start
I knew it. She really
is my "Auntie Witch."

00:48:53.609 --> 00:48:55.711 position:19% line:89% align:start
Hey, this painting...

00:48:55.744 --> 00:48:56.946 position:21% line:89% align:start
Do you recognize it?

00:48:56.980 --> 00:49:00.749 position:5% line:83% align:start
Yeah, I do. It's the one you've
been restoring for so long.

00:49:04.120 --> 00:49:05.788 position:38% line:83% align:start
[KAZUKO]
It's a strange painting.

00:49:05.822 --> 00:49:07.689 position:13% line:89% align:start
The longer you look at it,

00:49:07.723 --> 00:49:11.261 position:21% line:83% align:start
the more relaxed and
comforted you feel.

00:49:11.294 --> 00:49:12.829 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
Mm.

00:49:13.695 --> 00:49:15.865 position:19% line:83% align:start
[KAZUKO] We don't know
who the painter is,

00:49:15.899 --> 00:49:17.167 position:24% line:83% align:start
and we still don't
really know whether

00:49:17.200 --> 00:49:21.237 position:5% line:83% align:start
it's a worthy piece of art. But,
there's one thing I did learn

00:49:21.271 --> 00:49:24.140 position:27% line:83% align:start
while working on
its restoration.

00:49:24.174 --> 00:49:26.910 position:19% line:83% align:start
This piece was painted
during a historical period

00:49:26.943 --> 00:49:30.046 position:24% line:83% align:start
of famine and war
many centuries ago.

00:49:30.080 --> 00:49:32.315 position:44% line:89% align:start
Oh?

00:49:32.348 --> 00:49:33.850 position:38% line:83% align:start
[KAZUKO]
I wonder how someone was

00:49:33.883 --> 00:49:36.686 position:21% line:83% align:start
able to create such
a beautiful painting

00:49:36.719 --> 00:49:41.057 position:10% line:83% align:start
when it must've seemed that
the world was coming to an end?

00:50:17.361 --> 00:50:19.096 position:24% line:83% align:start
[FUKUSHIMA-SENSEI]
What're you gonna do, Konno?

00:50:19.130 --> 00:50:22.732 position:7% line:83% align:start
You're the only one who hasn't
chosen your academic major.

00:50:23.901 --> 00:50:25.236 position:24% line:83% align:start
[FUKUSHIMA-SENSEI]
Konno...

00:50:26.703 --> 00:50:28.038 position:24% line:83% align:start
[FUKUSHIMA-SENSEI]
Konno!

00:50:28.839 --> 00:50:30.207 position:10% line:83% align:start
--[FUKUSHIMA-SENSEI] Konno!
--Yes!

00:50:30.241 --> 00:50:31.774 position:13% line:89% align:start
Don't get all cocky on me

00:50:31.809 --> 00:50:34.145 position:13% line:83% align:start
just 'cause you got a good
mark on the math quiz.

00:50:34.178 --> 00:50:35.712 position:38% line:89% align:start
I won't!

00:50:41.852 --> 00:50:44.989 position:24% line:89% align:start
That's so weird...

00:50:45.022 --> 00:50:48.993 position:21% line:83% align:start
I swear it said "90"
last time I saw it.

00:50:49.026 --> 00:50:50.928 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:50:50.961 --> 00:50:52.763 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MORIKO]
Why don't we ask her ourselves?

00:50:52.796 --> 00:50:53.697 position:41% line:83% align:start
[KAHO]
I dunno...

00:50:53.731 --> 00:50:56.867 position:33% line:83% align:start
--Ask what?
--W-Wait! Hang on a second!

00:50:56.901 --> 00:50:58.736 position:10% line:89% align:start
Wh-Whoa! What's this about?!

00:50:58.769 --> 00:51:01.705 position:10% line:83% align:start
Makoto Konno! We are members
of the Volunteer Club! And we--

00:51:01.739 --> 00:51:04.308 position:7% line:83% align:start
[SEKIMI] And there's something
we'd like to ask you!

00:51:04.341 --> 00:51:05.976 position:16% line:89% align:start
Nevermind. It's nothing!

00:51:06.010 --> 00:51:07.978 position:13% line:83% align:start
We have noticed something
about you lately.

00:51:08.012 --> 00:51:09.280 position:10% line:89% align:start
You're always with Kousuke!

00:51:09.313 --> 00:51:10.748 position:38% line:89% align:start
Uh-huh?

00:51:10.781 --> 00:51:12.850 position:19% line:83% align:start
So, are you two going
steady then, or what?!

00:51:12.883 --> 00:51:13.552 position:10% line:89% align:start
Are you going out with him?

00:51:13.585 --> 00:51:15.119 position:5% line:89% align:start
Are you going out with Kousuke?

00:51:15.152 --> 00:51:17.289 position:27% line:83% align:start
[SEKIMI, MORIKO]
Are you going out with him?!

00:51:22.893 --> 00:51:25.263 position:19% line:83% align:start
[KAHO] I was still in
junior high at the time,

00:51:25.297 --> 00:51:27.765 position:10% line:83% align:start
but apparently some students
from the Volunteer Club

00:51:27.798 --> 00:51:30.935 position:5% line:83% align:start
at Kuranose Senior High had gone
to visit the retirement home

00:51:30.968 --> 00:51:33.037 position:10% line:89% align:start
where my grandmother lived.

00:51:33.071 --> 00:51:36.374 position:5% line:83% align:start
Grandma was especially impressed
with one of the students,

00:51:36.408 --> 00:51:39.144 position:21% line:83% align:start
and she spoke to me
about him many times.

00:51:39.177 --> 00:51:40.312 position:19% line:89% align:start
She would go on and on

00:51:40.345 --> 00:51:43.281 position:19% line:83% align:start
about what a kind and
gentle boy he was.

00:51:43.315 --> 00:51:45.816 position:13% line:89% align:start
She said it over and over.

00:51:48.186 --> 00:51:49.988 position:41% line:83% align:start
[KAHO]
This might sound strange, but,

00:51:50.021 --> 00:51:51.456 position:7% line:89% align:start
she talked so much about him,

00:51:51.489 --> 00:51:53.892 position:21% line:83% align:start
that I began to kind
of fall in love.

00:51:53.925 --> 00:51:56.161 position:27% line:83% align:start
Even though I'd
never even met him.

00:51:56.194 --> 00:51:58.263 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
That's a sweet story.

00:51:58.296 --> 00:52:01.132 position:27% line:83% align:start
I found out when
I got into senior high

00:52:01.166 --> 00:52:04.369 position:16% line:83% align:start
that that student's name
was Kousuke Tsuda.

00:52:04.402 --> 00:52:06.838 position:19% line:83% align:start
Wow, things like that
really do happen.

00:52:06.871 --> 00:52:10.141 position:5% line:83% align:start
The problem is that Kaho's shy.
She's afraid of her own shadow.

00:52:10.175 --> 00:52:12.077 position:19% line:83% align:start
We've been working to
drum up her courage.

00:52:12.110 --> 00:52:15.046 position:19% line:83% align:start
And finally, finally,
we got her to tell Kousuke

00:52:15.080 --> 00:52:15.947 position:13% line:89% align:start
she's got a crush on him.

00:52:15.981 --> 00:52:17.115 position:10% line:89% align:start
Oh, you mean the other day?

00:52:17.148 --> 00:52:19.184 position:10% line:89% align:start
But, according to Kousuke...

00:52:19.217 --> 00:52:21.386 position:41% line:89% align:start
Huh?!

00:52:21.419 --> 00:52:24.155 position:21% line:83% align:start
"I've already given
my heart to someone!"

00:52:24.189 --> 00:52:26.559 position:16% line:83% align:start
"I'm sorry, but I cannot
go out with you!"

00:52:26.592 --> 00:52:27.993 position:27% line:89% align:start
No, wait... Uh!

00:52:28.026 --> 00:52:30.095 position:5% line:83% align:start
--That's not really how it went.
--Huh?

00:52:30.128 --> 00:52:33.231 position:5% line:83% align:start
"How could an bonehead like that
get a higher mark than I did?"

00:52:33.265 --> 00:52:36.369 position:13% line:83% align:start
"I've gotta stop slacking
off so much. Sorry."

00:52:36.402 --> 00:52:39.338 position:24% line:83% align:start
So he apologized,
and turned me down.

00:52:42.874 --> 00:52:46.011 position:13% line:83% align:start
Who's the bonehead he was
talking about. Is it me?

00:52:46.044 --> 00:52:47.446 position:27% line:83% align:start
And that's when
Kousuke told us.

00:52:47.480 --> 00:52:49.215 position:19% line:83% align:start
He said that he wasn't
going out with you,

00:52:49.248 --> 00:52:50.815 position:5% line:89% align:start
but I'm not sure we believe him.

00:52:50.849 --> 00:52:52.518 position:16% line:83% align:start
So how 'bout explaining
what's going on then?!

00:52:52.551 --> 00:52:54.553 position:19% line:83% align:start
Something doesn't seem
right if you ask me!

00:52:54.587 --> 00:52:56.589 position:5% line:89% align:start
Time you gave us an explanation!

00:52:56.622 --> 00:52:58.324 position:24% line:89% align:start
Hang on a minute!

00:52:58.357 --> 00:53:01.294 position:24% line:83% align:start
Okay! You've made
your point already!

00:53:01.327 --> 00:53:04.263 position:27% line:83% align:start
Ahem! I'll deal
with this somehow.

00:53:04.297 --> 00:53:05.431 position:27% line:89% align:start
Deal with this?

00:53:05.464 --> 00:53:07.600 position:13% line:89% align:start
What do you mean, somehow?

00:53:07.633 --> 00:53:09.268 position:30% line:89% align:start
Just trust me!

00:53:09.302 --> 00:53:11.871 position:27% line:89% align:start
[MAKOTO panting]

00:53:11.904 --> 00:53:16.275 position:35% line:89% align:start
[growling]

00:53:16.309 --> 00:53:17.877 position:44% line:89% align:start
Ha!

00:53:21.314 --> 00:53:23.182 position:27% line:89% align:start
[MAKOTO grunts]

00:53:23.215 --> 00:53:26.185 position:24% line:89% align:start
[STUDENTS murmur]

00:53:28.954 --> 00:53:31.991 position:33% line:89% align:start
Uh... Hi...

00:53:32.024 --> 00:53:33.359 position:41% line:89% align:start
Kaho!

00:53:33.392 --> 00:53:34.927 position:44% line:89% align:start
Uh.

00:53:34.960 --> 00:53:36.562 position:44% line:89% align:start
I...

00:53:36.663 --> 00:53:39.198 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MAKOTO]
Kousuke!

00:53:39.231 --> 00:53:40.866 position:38% line:89% align:start
Uh-huh?

00:53:40.900 --> 00:53:42.134 position:19% line:83% align:start
